WEBVTT

00:04.040 --> 00:07.749
Margarita on the house
for the old married couple!

00:07.750 --> 00:09.160
Happy anniversary.

00:09.170 --> 00:10.489
[ Distinguished accent ]
I thank you.

00:10.500 --> 00:13.287
[Taps glass ]
There. Excuse me.

00:13.290 --> 00:17.613
This is our 45th anniversary,
and, uh, I get to talk.

00:17.620 --> 00:20.077
She's finally coming out
of her shell. Quiet, everybody.

00:21.120 --> 00:22.109
Shh.

00:22.120 --> 00:23.417
Now, we're not
gonna sit here

00:23.420 --> 00:24.956
and tell you guys
how great we are.

00:24.960 --> 00:26.609
You're gonna do it!

00:26.620 --> 00:28.611
I want somebody
to make a toast.

00:28.620 --> 00:29.780
I'll do it.

00:29.790 --> 00:31.997
Oh, pipe down, everyone.
Forrest Gump's talking.

00:33.330 --> 00:35.321
I just wanna say
how amazing it is

00:35.330 --> 00:37.662
to see a marriage
that lasts 45 years.

00:37.670 --> 00:40.207
And, Mom and Dad, you set
a great example for all of us,

00:40.210 --> 00:42.326
and it's a pretty high bar.

00:42.330 --> 00:44.036
I mean,
Darlene couldn't get over it,

00:44.040 --> 00:45.496
and Beclq's stuck under it,

00:45.500 --> 00:48.162
and my marriage is --
it's not really a picnic.

00:48.170 --> 00:48.989
I mean, my w--

00:50.750 --> 00:52.911
Thank you!

00:52.920 --> 00:55.957
Anyway, Mom and Dad,
happy 45th.

00:55.960 --> 00:58.918
Oh, Becky, since you're
our waitress for this evening,

00:58.920 --> 01:01.241
do you guys have any special
anniversary song here?

01:01.250 --> 01:03.741
Nice try.
We only do birthdays.

01:03.750 --> 01:06.537
-What a coincidence.
-Don't do it.

01:06.540 --> 01:08.451
It's my birthday today!

01:08.460 --> 01:09.996
Yay!

01:10.000 --> 01:12.616
Hey, everybody!
It's Darlene's birthday!

01:12.620 --> 01:14.201
She's 60!

01:16.120 --> 01:19.669
[ To tune of "Happy Birthday" ]
Feliz cumpleaos a ti

01:19.670 --> 01:23.288
Feliz cumpleaos a ti

01:23.290 --> 01:24.826
Feliz cumpleaos

01:24.830 --> 01:26.707
A Darlene

01:28.120 --> 01:31.829
iFeliz cumpleaos a ti!

01:31.830 --> 01:34.663
_ Ay-yi-yi-yi-
yI-yI-yI-yi-yi-yi-yi.

01:34.670 --> 01:36.206
Thank you!

01:36.210 --> 01:37.666
Ah.

01:37.670 --> 01:39.786
So, are you guys doing anything
special for your anniversary?

01:39.790 --> 01:41.109
You got to do something.

01:41.120 --> 01:43.497
45 years -- I mean, people get
less than that for murder.

01:43.500 --> 01:44.615
[ Laughs ]

01:49.500 --> 01:51.377
Oh, I got it!

01:53.330 --> 01:55.412
Wait, do you guys get points
on your credit card?

01:55.420 --> 01:58.162
We get threats.
Is that the same thing?

01:58.170 --> 02:00.661
[ Chuckles ] No, you get points
for every dollar that you spend.

02:00.670 --> 02:02.069
It's like a reward.

02:02.080 --> 02:04.617
You can use 'em for, like,
travel or to buy things.

02:04.620 --> 02:06.827
Yeah, you can stay
at some nice hotel in the city

02:06.830 --> 02:08.457
for your anniversary.

02:08.460 --> 02:10.109
Put in
your password, Dad.

02:10.120 --> 02:12.281
Let's_ see
how many pomts we have.

02:12.290 --> 02:14.246
Well, this is
the credit card we used

02:14.250 --> 02:16.036
to pay off
all the other credit cards,

02:16.040 --> 02:17.917
so we probably got
a bunch.

02:17.920 --> 02:22.914
We got enough for one night
at the Radford Suites,

02:22.920 --> 02:24.706
with points
left over for --

02:24.710 --> 02:26.200
[ Gasps ]

02:26.210 --> 02:28.201
H-Hold me, Mama,
'cause I'm fit to bust --

02:28.210 --> 02:30.201
a Honey Baked ham!

02:31.460 --> 02:33.530
Did I mention
the hotel has a pool?

02:33.540 --> 02:35.451
Like if you had a ham
and a room,

02:35.460 --> 02:37.371
you'd ever come out of there
to swim.

02:38.920 --> 02:40.160
[ Laughs ]

02:40.170 --> 02:42.411
All right.
I'm booking it.

02:42.420 --> 02:44.320
And, as my anniversary present
to you guys,

02:44.330 --> 02:45.740
I'll babysit the kids.

02:45.750 --> 02:49.709
It's not babysitting
when they're yours!

03:23.000 --> 03:25.070
[ Dan and Roseanne laughing ]

03:27.290 --> 03:31.033
_"Roseanne" is recorded live
In front of a studio audience.

03:31.040 --> 03:32.951
Right,
we'll be there at 3:00.

03:32.960 --> 03:34.746
And it's our anniversary,

03:34.750 --> 03:37.787
so I really want this
to be special.

03:37.790 --> 03:41.908
I want to reserve the biggest,
nicest one you got.

03:41.920 --> 03:43.615
Just like we had
on our wedding night.

03:43.620 --> 03:44.951
Is that the hotel?

03:44.960 --> 03:46.325
No, it's the ham people.

03:46.330 --> 03:48.241
Oh.

03:48.250 --> 03:50.115
We're picking one up
on the way.

03:50.120 --> 03:52.873
Thank you. Thank --

03:52.880 --> 03:55.166
You have
a Honey Baked day, too.

03:56.830 --> 03:59.242
Hey, we got a problem.

03:59.250 --> 04:01.457
Two, if you don't think
leftover Chinese food

04:01.460 --> 04:03.746
belongs in an omelette.

04:03.750 --> 04:04.876
My knee is killing me,

04:04.880 --> 04:06.700
and a bunch of my pain pills
are missing.

04:06.710 --> 04:08.200
[ Light rattling ]

04:08.210 --> 04:10.075
This thing was,
like, half full.

04:10.080 --> 04:11.616
How many did you take?

04:11.620 --> 04:13.451
Just a couple for my back.

04:13.460 --> 04:15.610
Are you sure you didn't take
more than you thought?

04:15.620 --> 04:17.497
If I was taking
handsful of these pills,

04:17.500 --> 04:20.822
I'd be
in a way better mood.

04:20.830 --> 04:24.743
Have you noticed me
in a way better mood, Dan?

04:24.750 --> 04:26.286
The only thing
I've noticed

04:26.290 --> 04:27.996
is that I love you more
every day.

04:29.330 --> 04:30.661
Sir.

04:32.500 --> 04:34.161
Well, somebody
must have taken 'em,

04:34.170 --> 04:35.740
so we have to find out
who It was.

04:35.750 --> 04:38.662
We have a serious opioid problem
in this country.

04:38.670 --> 04:43.164
Let's examine who else had
access to the narcotics!

04:44.420 --> 04:47.207
Everybody in this house.

04:47.210 --> 04:49.781
You know, back in the day,
I busted up a hashish ring

04:49.790 --> 04:53.908
in the -- in the Model U.N.
down at the junior high.

04:53.920 --> 04:55.285
[ Clears throat ]

04:55.290 --> 04:57.576
It was Luxembourg.

04:57.580 --> 04:59.878
[ Chuckles ]
It's always Luxembourg.

05:01.380 --> 05:03.746
Darlene!

05:03.750 --> 05:05.991
Good morning.

05:06.000 --> 05:07.820
What brings you
to the kitchen?

05:09.670 --> 05:12.878
_ I was _
followmg a rainbow.

05:12.880 --> 05:14.416
Uh, I just came down
for coffee.

05:14.420 --> 05:17.116
Mm. Interesting.
Because you're groggy?

05:17.120 --> 05:19.782
Unable to deal
with the real world?

05:19.790 --> 05:22.111
Oh, my God.
Are you selling vitamins again?

05:24.120 --> 05:26.327
Some of your mom's pain pills
are missing.

05:26.330 --> 05:28.070
Oh, well, I don't
take pills of any kind.

05:28.080 --> 05:29.411
I don't like to feel
out of control,

05:29.420 --> 05:31.240
or I can't manage
my multinational empire.

05:32.830 --> 05:35.242
How come_ there's sweet-and-sour
shrimp In the eggs?

05:35.250 --> 05:37.457
You know, I don't think
I've noticed before --

05:37.460 --> 05:40.202
are you wearing
eyelash extensions?

05:40.210 --> 05:42.166
I literally
can't even afford ChapStick.

05:42.170 --> 05:43.285
Oh.

05:43.290 --> 05:46.282
Because your natural lashes
are fantastic.

05:46.290 --> 05:47.325
Open up your eyes
real wide.

05:49.670 --> 05:52.241
Hmm. No slurred speech
or pinpoint pupils.

05:52.250 --> 05:53.376
Mom, what is this?

05:53.380 --> 05:54.950
She's clean!

05:56.420 --> 05:59.457
We're never gonna find out
anything like this, Rose.

05:59.460 --> 06:01.917
There's been a ton of people
through this house.

06:01.920 --> 06:04.821
Let's just hide the pills
in a safer place.

06:04.830 --> 06:06.741
Well, that doesn't solve
my problem.

06:06.750 --> 06:09.878
I can't get a damn refill
for two more weeks,

06:09.880 --> 06:12.610
and my knee is
holding a gun to my head.

06:12.620 --> 06:14.281
Well, I could go
to my doctor

06:14.290 --> 06:15.951
and tell him
my back's flared up again.

06:15.960 --> 06:19.202
That's so sweet.

06:19.210 --> 06:22.748
Tonight I'm gonna give your back
a reason to flare up.

06:25.460 --> 06:27.200
[ French accent ]
Zut alors!

06:28.920 --> 06:30.069
[ Doorbell rings ]

06:32.250 --> 06:33.376
Hey, Crystal.

06:33.380 --> 06:34.950
Hey!

06:39.170 --> 06:41.070
Hey, everybody.

06:41.080 --> 06:43.207
Guess what today is.

06:43.210 --> 06:44.916
A fundraiser
for your dignity?

06:44.920 --> 06:47.741
No, no, no.
You're such a stitch.

06:47.750 --> 06:50.571
It's my last day
before I retire!

06:50.580 --> 06:52.878
All right!

06:52.880 --> 06:54.700
It's about time.

06:54.710 --> 06:58.168
You've been working that saloon
since when, 1865?

06:59.420 --> 07:00.876
Give her a break,
Roseanne.

07:00.880 --> 07:02.780
There's a cattle drive
a-comIn' through town,

07:02.790 --> 07:04.781
and Miss Kitty wants her
to be real friendly-like

07:04.790 --> 07:06.667
to all the cowpokes.

07:06.670 --> 07:09.241
Laugh all you want,
but I'm about to start living

07:09.250 --> 07:10.535
the best years
of my life.

07:10.540 --> 07:13.953
I'm retiring from the casino
with full benefits!

07:13.960 --> 07:16.667
-Fu|| benefits?
-That's amazing, Crystal.

07:16.670 --> 07:18.069
No one has that
nowadays.

07:19.380 --> 07:22.247
I brought you champagne
for tonight.

07:22.250 --> 07:24.457
Hey, Crystal.

07:24.460 --> 07:26.826
Uh, I didn't know exactly when
the women's movement would end,

07:26.830 --> 07:28.991
but now seems like _
a pretty good tIme to call It.

07:30.380 --> 07:33.076
Hey, Darlene,
you still looking for work?

07:33.080 --> 07:36.072
'Cause if I recommend you for
my job, you're as good as in.

07:36.080 --> 07:38.036
Aw, that's really sweet,
Crystal.

07:38.040 --> 07:41.328
Did I mention the benefits
package includes mental health?

07:41.330 --> 07:43.571
I just found out
I hate my mother.

07:43.580 --> 07:46.162
Which is really weird
because I love my mother.

07:48.380 --> 07:50.610
Wait, you have
full benefits?

07:50.620 --> 07:52.781
If you don't want it, Darlene,
I'll take it.

07:53.750 --> 07:55.615
Um, you know what?

07:55.620 --> 07:58.748
I-I appreciate the offer,
but it's not really my thing,

07:58.750 --> 08:00.320
so go for it, Beck.

08:00.330 --> 08:02.321
If you don't feel like you're
betraying your Mexican heritage.

08:07.120 --> 08:09.668
Are you sure you want
to turn that job down?

08:09.670 --> 08:12.958
For full dental and medical,
I'd wear that dress.

08:12.960 --> 08:14.666
Oh, well, you got to that
pretty quick.

08:14.670 --> 08:16.535
Anything you want
to tell me, Dad?

08:16.540 --> 08:18.576
I gotta be honest,
Darlene,

08:18.580 --> 08:21.708
I don't know how you can pass
on a job with full benefits.

08:21.710 --> 08:23.917
Uh, I have
some pretty good reasons.

08:23.920 --> 08:26.241
Shall we start with
the riverboat-whore vibe?

08:27.830 --> 08:30.879
Hey, you know who wasn't
too good to wear that dress?

08:30.880 --> 08:32.996
One Mr. Bugs Bunny.

08:34.670 --> 08:36.786
Dad, I still want to be
a writer.

08:36.790 --> 08:39.827
I mean, I've gone from novels
to textbooks to menus.

08:39.830 --> 08:43.038
If I take this waitress job,
I'm just giving up completely.

08:43.040 --> 08:44.951
What are you gonna do
if your kids get sick,
write about it?

08:44.960 --> 08:47.030
Well,
we managed so far.

08:47.040 --> 08:50.203
You've been lucky.
One emergency can wipe you out.

08:50.210 --> 08:52.110
You know what I'd give right now
to have full coverage

08:52.120 --> 08:54.031
for your mother's knee?

08:54.040 --> 08:55.826
Sometimes you just
gotta suck it up

08:55.830 --> 08:57.036
and put your family first.

08:58.500 --> 09:00.536
Okay.
You made your point.

09:01.500 --> 09:03.661
Good.

09:03.670 --> 09:06.992
I know a little bit
about how this world works.

09:08.380 --> 09:10.416
I got to go
jam a sleep-apnea mask

09:10.420 --> 09:12.706
and a seven-pound ham
into an overnight bag.

09:18.920 --> 09:20.285
Good evening.

09:20.290 --> 09:21.951
Checking in.

09:21.960 --> 09:22.995
Points?

09:25.620 --> 09:26.871
Last name?

09:26.880 --> 09:29.030
Hilton.

09:29.040 --> 09:31.281
Staying
under the name Conner.

09:31.290 --> 09:34.373
Perfect.
I have you right here.

09:34.380 --> 09:36.871
We have a superior deluxe room
with a view.

09:36.880 --> 09:38.780
Ooh!
Were we upgraded?

09:38.790 --> 09:40.200
Oh, no, sir.

09:40.210 --> 09:42.826
"Superior deluxe"
is our lowest level room.

09:42.830 --> 09:45.162
You have a mini-bar,

09:45.170 --> 09:48.742
and you also have 24-hour access
to our business center.

09:48.750 --> 09:51.241
Oh, great. I can't wait
'til we're checked in, Dan,

09:51.250 --> 09:54.162
so we can get down there
to the business center.

09:54.170 --> 09:55.785
Capital idea.

09:55.790 --> 10:00.409
I need to fax a copy of my ass
to our associates in Singapore.

10:02.830 --> 10:06.322
If I could just get
a credit card for incidentals?

10:06.330 --> 10:08.537
For who?

10:08.540 --> 10:11.577
The points cover the room,
but the card is in case

10:11.580 --> 10:15.414
you want to order room service
or purchase a movie.

10:15.420 --> 10:19.993
Oh, sure. I-I guess...
I'll just use this one.

10:20.000 --> 10:22.616
Our platinum card's
in the shop.

10:22.620 --> 10:23.450
[ Chuckling ] Okay.

10:25.830 --> 10:27.821
Do I smell ham?

10:30.710 --> 10:32.450
Hm.

10:32.460 --> 10:35.167
I'm sorry, sir.
This card was declined.

10:35.170 --> 10:36.876
Would you like to try
another one?

10:36.880 --> 10:38.416
Uh, listen here,
my good man,

10:38.420 --> 10:39.910
we won't be getting
any incidents,

10:39.920 --> 10:42.787
so you can just skip
that part.

10:42.790 --> 10:43.870
Oh, I'm sorry.

10:43.880 --> 10:47.031
I-I can't check you in
without a credit card.

10:47.040 --> 10:49.827
It's just the policy
of the hotel.

10:49.830 --> 10:52.537
And every hotel
in the world.

10:52.540 --> 10:55.373
What the hell's
this country coming to

10:55.380 --> 10:58.167
when you need money
to get free stuff?

10:58.170 --> 10:59.489
Let me tell ya
something,

10:59.500 --> 11:01.821
I don't even want
to stay here now.

11:01.830 --> 11:03.707
I just want to go home.

11:03.710 --> 11:05.450
And if you saw
where we live,

11:05.460 --> 11:07.746
you would know
what an insult that is.

11:10.420 --> 11:12.615
Look at this.

11:12.620 --> 11:14.326
This is not who I am.

11:17.960 --> 11:21.202
It's what
you've made me!

11:24.250 --> 11:27.242
You know,
screw that hotel.

11:27.250 --> 11:29.707
The two most important things
about our anniversary

11:29.710 --> 11:30.699
are right here.

11:30.710 --> 11:32.610
What, me and ham?

11:32.620 --> 11:34.076
[ Laughs ]

11:34.080 --> 11:36.116
I was gonna say
"liquor and ham,"

11:36.120 --> 11:37.451
but I'm glad
you joined us.

11:38.540 --> 11:40.030
And now...

11:41.830 --> 11:43.286
[ Cork pops ]

11:43.290 --> 11:44.700
...Mexican champagne.

11:44.710 --> 11:46.917
Ooh!

11:46.920 --> 11:50.117
It's pink.
I guess that's the salsa.

11:52.290 --> 11:53.951
Does Madame approve?

11:53.960 --> 11:56.076
Hells, yeah,
Madame does!

11:58.120 --> 12:01.248
To the woman
who makes It a pleasure

12:01.250 --> 12:02.911
to wake up
every morning.

12:04.290 --> 12:06.076
Here's to you,
Little Debbie.

12:09.250 --> 12:10.740
-Yes!
-Who wants whipped cream?

12:10.750 --> 12:12.069
Me.

12:12.080 --> 12:14.287
Where are
my baby birds?

12:23.540 --> 12:24.825
Just for the kids.

12:24.830 --> 12:26.786
[ Groans ]

12:28.420 --> 12:29.910
Hey, look.

12:29.920 --> 12:32.491
When you connect the dots,
it makes a giant bean.

12:32.500 --> 12:34.991
You couldn't tell that
without connecting the dots?

12:38.460 --> 12:42.328
-Hey, chica.
-Hey, gringa.

12:42.330 --> 12:46.073
So, while I have you alone
for a minute, um...

12:46.080 --> 12:48.071
I've really been thinking
about it,

12:48.080 --> 12:50.492
and I'd be pretty irresponsible
not to go after that job.

12:51.750 --> 12:53.820
It doesn't work like that.

12:53.830 --> 12:55.991
You can't say
you don't want a job one day

12:56.000 --> 12:58.116
and then turn around
and say you want It.

12:58.120 --> 13:00.918
Well, I see you're well-versed
in labor law.

13:00.920 --> 13:02.706
I don't have
any other options.

13:04.420 --> 13:07.457
You don't need this job.
You have a college degree.

13:07.460 --> 13:10.202
Well, unfortunately,
Walmart has no more openings

13:10.210 --> 13:11.666
in their English Lit
department.

13:12.960 --> 13:16.111
You still have a better chance
of finding something than I do.

13:16.120 --> 13:18.247
I don't know what to say, Becky.
I'm not doing this for me.

13:18.250 --> 13:19.740
My kids need
medical and dental.

13:19.750 --> 13:21.035
Don't you want them
to have that?

13:21.040 --> 13:22.371
So because you have kids,

13:22.380 --> 13:24.780
my problems will never be
as important as yours?

13:24.790 --> 13:26.109
Oh, you're right.

13:26.120 --> 13:28.111
Us single moms have had it
too easy for too long.

13:28.120 --> 13:29.997
Uh, you might want
to get back there.

13:30.000 --> 13:32.491
Harris found some dirty phrases
in the word search,

13:32.500 --> 13:34.536
and now the little_ones
are asking questions.

13:47.080 --> 13:48.911
[ Roseanne laughs ]

13:48.920 --> 13:51.912
Hey, my turn
to spin the bottle now.

13:51.920 --> 13:53.035
Okay.

13:54.420 --> 13:55.455
Ohh!

13:55.460 --> 13:56.279
Oh!

13:56.290 --> 13:57.109
[ Laughs ]

13:57.120 --> 13:58.781
You got
to kiss the ham.

13:58.790 --> 14:01.031
[ Laughs ]

14:01.040 --> 14:02.576
I've kissed worse.

14:02.580 --> 14:05.879
[ Laughs ]

14:05.880 --> 14:08.496
Mmm! Oohmm!

14:09.790 --> 14:11.576
[ Laughing ]

14:14.710 --> 14:16.575
What's so funny?

14:18.750 --> 14:20.661
[ Snorts ] Oh!

14:20.670 --> 14:24.663
"Ham" is spelled the same way
frontward and backward.

14:24.670 --> 14:25.534
[ Laughs ]

14:25.540 --> 14:27.496
Wow.

14:27.500 --> 14:30.412
Methinks the lady
hath been overserved.

14:30.420 --> 14:32.160
[ Laughing ]

14:34.880 --> 14:36.780
Arf!

14:36.790 --> 14:39.611
[ Growls, barks ]

14:39.620 --> 14:41.451
Are you growling at me?

14:41.460 --> 14:42.745
Ruff!

14:42.750 --> 14:44.456
I see how this is.

14:44.460 --> 14:46.451
It's time to take this party
to the bedroom.

14:46.460 --> 14:48.030
[ Laughs ]

14:48.040 --> 14:49.530
Arf!

14:49.540 --> 14:50.575
[ Growls ]

14:50.580 --> 14:51.410
Down, girl.

14:52.880 --> 14:54.165
[ Growls ]

14:54.170 --> 14:55.785
Oh!

14:55.790 --> 14:57.530
I gotta tell you,

14:57.540 --> 14:59.701
I don't even recognize
what it is we're doing anymore.

14:59.710 --> 15:01.746
[ Laughing ]

15:01.750 --> 15:04.207
What the hell, Rose?

15:04.210 --> 15:05.666
You only had
a couple of drinks.

15:05.670 --> 15:07.956
[ Laughs ]

15:07.960 --> 15:09.996
Well, it's not my fault.

15:10.000 --> 15:12.571
The champagne on the Vicodin
should say

15:12.580 --> 15:14.491
"Do not take with label."

15:14.500 --> 15:16.912
[ Laughs ]

15:16.920 --> 15:20.572
But the good news is
my knees are gone!

15:20.580 --> 15:21.820
[ Laughs ]

15:21.830 --> 15:24.162
How could you possibly have
taken more Vicodin?

15:24.170 --> 15:26.115
I didn't even get
the prescription yet.

15:26.120 --> 15:28.281
Well,
you better get on it,

15:28.290 --> 15:31.669
because my secret bottles
are running low.

15:34.460 --> 15:36.701
Hey, you look like
my husband.

15:43.620 --> 15:44.780
Hi.

15:44.790 --> 15:46.997
Busy. Can't talk now.

15:47.000 --> 15:49.616
I got an 8% tip
riding on this.

15:50.580 --> 15:52.070
Wait.

15:52.080 --> 15:54.321
Crystal called me.

15:54.330 --> 15:56.457
Thank you so much
for not going after that job.

15:56.460 --> 15:58.280
You don't have to
thank me.

15:58.290 --> 16:00.326
I didn't want
to leave here anyway.

16:00.330 --> 16:02.378
We just got
cream-filled churros.

16:04.380 --> 16:06.166
It's an exciting time.

16:09.120 --> 16:12.283
Okay. Um...
I won't thank you.

16:12.290 --> 16:14.201
But I will give you
a gift.

16:14.210 --> 16:17.031
[ Gasps ] Brochures?
Thanks!

16:17.040 --> 16:18.416
I've seen these
at the bank,

16:18.420 --> 16:20.411
but I never dreamed
of owning one.

16:20.420 --> 16:22.570
Just read it, dork.

16:22.580 --> 16:25.378
There's a program in
hotel and restaurant management

16:25.380 --> 16:27.371
at U of I, St. Charles,
and I checked into it.

16:27.380 --> 16:29.075
You qualify
for a state grant

16:29.080 --> 16:31.207
because, luckily,
you're poor and old.

16:31.210 --> 16:33.917
I work full time. I don't
have time to go to school.

16:33.920 --> 16:37.663
But they have night classes,
or you can do it online.

16:37.670 --> 16:41.242
Come on, Beclq. You were
always so great in school.

16:41.250 --> 16:43.070
I'm 43 years old.

16:43.080 --> 16:45.412
Okay, so in two years,

16:45.420 --> 16:48.287
you can be a 45-year-old
waitress hustling for tips

16:48.290 --> 16:50.497
or you can be a 45-year-old
with a degree

16:50.500 --> 16:52.491
pulling down
almost six figures a year.

16:52.500 --> 16:55.242
And look, between classes,
you can sit under a tree

16:55.250 --> 16:57.320
and play guitar
with one friend of every color.

17:00.000 --> 17:01.786
I gotta get back to work.

17:01.790 --> 17:03.075
I'll think about it.

17:03.080 --> 17:04.069
Okay.

17:04.080 --> 17:05.240
Okay.

17:09.540 --> 17:10.780
Thank you.

17:12.670 --> 17:15.571
All right, I thinkI have
one more thing to show you.

17:15.580 --> 17:16.956
[ Sighs ]

17:16.960 --> 17:19.997
I know you gave up
a lot for me, so...

17:20.000 --> 17:22.491
I feel I owe you this.

17:22.500 --> 17:23.819
[ Laughs ]

17:32.000 --> 17:33.786
Good morning.

17:33.790 --> 17:36.076
Afternoon, actually.

17:36.080 --> 17:37.741
You okay?

17:37.750 --> 17:39.570
My mouth hurts.

17:39.580 --> 17:41.707
That's because the tug-ofâ€”war
over the ham bone

17:41.710 --> 17:43.951
took 20 minutes.

17:43.960 --> 17:45.416
When did that happen?

17:45.420 --> 17:47.069
Right after you tried
to eat my pants.

17:49.420 --> 17:50.910
Let's talk.

17:50.920 --> 17:53.571
Not until I get a pill.
I'm hurtin'.

17:53.580 --> 17:55.616
You want pills?

17:55.620 --> 17:56.496
[ Loud rattling ]

17:56.500 --> 17:57.740
I got pills.

17:59.830 --> 18:01.286
Wow.

18:01.290 --> 18:03.702
That's a lot of pills,
Dan.

18:03.710 --> 18:06.326
I think
you might have a problem.

18:06.330 --> 18:08.286
I do have a problem.

18:08.290 --> 18:10.372
I found these pills
hidden all over the house.

18:10.380 --> 18:12.575
Why don't you tell me
how big of a problem I have?

18:12.580 --> 18:15.879
Well, you already admitted
you have a problem,

18:15.880 --> 18:17.666
so that's your first step.

18:17.670 --> 18:19.490
So now you should go
find a meeting.

18:19.500 --> 18:20.740
Roseanne.

18:20.750 --> 18:23.287
[ Sighs ]
Okay, I'm in pain,

18:23.290 --> 18:25.076
so I take _
a few extra pills.

18:25.080 --> 18:27.241
It's not like
I'm a drug addict.

18:27.250 --> 18:28.410
Really?

18:28.420 --> 18:29.990
Who's Billy Kreski?

18:31.750 --> 18:33.706
His mom gave those to me.

18:33.710 --> 18:36.201
He got 'em when he got
his wisdom teeth out.

18:36.210 --> 18:37.370
If it wasn't for me,

18:37.380 --> 18:39.029
the kid might've got hooked
on pain pills.

18:40.460 --> 18:42.030
You're hoarding pills,

18:42.040 --> 18:44.326
you sent me out
for more,

18:44.330 --> 18:46.036
you blamed the kids --
all lies.

18:46.040 --> 18:47.496
45 years of marriage,

18:47.500 --> 18:49.377
you've never lied to me
like this before.

18:49.380 --> 18:50.449
Or have you?

18:50.460 --> 18:51.529
No.

18:53.330 --> 18:54.786
I just didn't
say anything

18:54.790 --> 18:56.667
because we can't afford
the surgery.

18:56.670 --> 18:58.035
And I got these pills

18:58.040 --> 19:01.282
'cause I'm gonna be dealing
with this for a long time.

19:01.290 --> 19:03.372
You don't have any idea
how bad it hurts.

19:03.380 --> 19:05.245
Yeah, I do.
I got a bad back.

19:05.250 --> 19:06.535
And when your back
goes out,

19:06.540 --> 19:08.280
you lay on the couch
for two weeks,

19:08.290 --> 19:09.871
and I wait on you
hand and foot.

19:09.880 --> 19:11.700
You know what happens
when my knee hurts?

19:11.710 --> 19:14.702
I do the cleaning,
the shopping, the cooking --

19:14.710 --> 19:16.166
Fine!
I'll do all that.

19:16.170 --> 19:17.740
Just show me
where the water bucket is

19:17.750 --> 19:20.378
and the sponge
on the stick thingy.

19:20.380 --> 19:22.029
I'll cut back.

19:22.040 --> 19:23.826
No, you won't.

19:23.830 --> 19:26.037
You're taking these
for more than pain.

19:27.920 --> 19:29.160
Book the surgery.

19:29.170 --> 19:30.455
[ Scoffs ]

19:30.460 --> 19:34.248
Where are we gonna get $3,000
for the deductible?

19:34.250 --> 19:35.740
Look, if it's between
you OD-ing

19:35.750 --> 19:38.378
and me coming up with the money,
I'll figure out something.

19:38.380 --> 19:42.612
In the meantime,
I'll give you one pill

19:42.620 --> 19:46.112
"every six to eight hours
for post-operative pain."

19:46.120 --> 19:47.610
What the hell?

19:47.620 --> 19:49.952
Are You sure Marcy Bellinger
doesn't need these?

19:51.620 --> 19:54.874
When you get new boobs,
compliments should be enough.

19:56.920 --> 19:58.569
I got to take a walk.

20:00.460 --> 20:02.325
I know
you can do this.

20:05.670 --> 20:08.616
[ Door opens, closes ]

20:08.620 --> 20:09.746
[ Groans softly ]

20:11.670 --> 20:12.910
[ Sighs ]

20:15.460 --> 20:17.280
Ohh.

20:20.080 --> 20:22.207
Oh, boy.

20:33.790 --> 20:35.610
[ Exhales sharply]

20:48.040 --> 20:49.996
Here's your Crown and diet,
ma'am.

20:53.080 --> 20:54.991
Thanks, drank skank.

20:56.080 --> 20:58.742
Ooh, you forgot my lemon.

20:58.750 --> 21:00.035
Would you be a dear?

21:00.040 --> 21:01.371
When I get back
with a lemon,

21:01.380 --> 21:03.075
are you gonna ask me
to bring you a lime?

21:03.080 --> 21:04.911
I wouldn't want
to have to tell the manager

21:04.920 --> 21:07.878
you mistreated me
on my...birthday.

21:09.420 --> 21:10.705
I'll be right back.

21:14.710 --> 21:17.497
Excuse me, sir.

21:17.500 --> 21:20.071
That blonde over there
asked me to give you her number,

21:20.080 --> 21:23.322
and she loves
when guys send pics.

21:23.330 --> 21:25.241
There you go.
Good luck.
